# Frontend Design System Rules

> Professional, enterprise-grade React + Next.js application using ShadCN, Tailwind, and Radix.
> Target aesthetic: Clean, minimal, technical, light-themed.

---

## 1. Typography

### Font Stack
- **Primary**: Use `IBM Plex Sans` (IBM's corporate typeface) for all UI text
- **Monospace**: Use `IBM Plex Mono` for code/technical content
- **Style**: Geometric, technical, highly legible
- **NEVER use**: Inter, Roboto, Arial, Geist, or generic sans-serif

### Installation
```bash
npm install @fontsource/ibm-plex-sans @fontsource/ibm-plex-mono
```

```tsx
// app/layout.tsx
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-sans/400.css";
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-sans/500.css";
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-sans/600.css";
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-sans/700.css";
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-mono/400.css";
import "@fontsource/ibm-plex-mono/500.css";
```

### Type Scale (use consistently)
```
text-xs    → 12px  — Labels, captions, metadata (tracking: 0.02em)
text-sm    → 14px  — Body text, form inputs, buttons (tracking: 0.01em)
text-base  → 16px  — Primary body, paragraphs (tracking: 0.01em)
text-lg    → 18px  — Section headers, emphasis (tracking: -0.01em)
text-xl    → 20px  — Page section titles (tracking: -0.02em)
text-2xl   → 24px  — Page headers (tracking: -0.025em)
text-3xl   → 30px  — Hero sections only (tracking: -0.03em)
```

### Font Weight Rules
- `font-normal` (400) — Body text, descriptions
- `font-medium` (500) — Buttons, labels, navigation, UI elements
- `font-semibold` (600) — Headings, emphasis
- `font-bold` (700) — Sparingly, only for critical emphasis
- **NEVER use**: font-black (900) in UI — too heavy

### Letter Spacing (Geometric Font Optimization)
- **Headings**: Tighter tracking (-0.02em to -0.03em) for geometric fonts
- **Body text**: Slightly looser (0.01em) for readability
- **Labels/UI**: Medium tracking (0.02em) for clarity at small sizes
- **Monospace**: No additional tracking (0)

