## 2. Color Palette

### Light Theme Foundation
Use a refined gray scale. NEVER use pure black (`#000`) or pure white (`#fff`) for backgrounds.

```css
/* tailwind.config.ts - extend colors */
gray: {
  50:  '#fafafa',  /* Page background */
  100: '#f4f4f5',  /* Card backgrounds, hover states */
  200: '#e4e4e7',  /* Borders, dividers */
  300: '#d4d4d8',  /* Disabled states */
  400: '#a1a1aa',  /* Placeholder text */
  500: '#71717a',  /* Secondary text */
  600: '#52525b',  /* Body text */
  700: '#3f3f46',  /* Primary text */
  800: '#27272a',  /* Headings */
  900: '#18181b',  /* High contrast text */
}
```

### Accent Colors
- **Primary**: Single accent color (blue, indigo, or brand color)
- Keep accent usage minimal — buttons, links, focus rings only
- Avoid gradients on white backgrounds (AI slop signature)

### Color Usage
```
Background:     gray-50 or white
Surface/Cards:  white with gray-200 border
Primary text:   gray-800 or gray-900
Secondary text: gray-500 or gray-600
Borders:        gray-200 (1px solid)
Focus rings:    ring-2 ring-offset-2 ring-gray-400
```

### FORBIDDEN
- Purple gradients on white backgrounds
- Rainbow or multi-color gradients
- Neon or overly saturated accent colors
- More than 2 accent colors in the entire app

